From these details the story of Barland’s Fffiz'stolac selectae. may be deduced. He began to work with E, as Martens had suggested. But when two-thirds of the book was already complete, Erasmus allowed him to make use of the text he had just revised for F, also contribut- ing a few of the new letters which he had selected for publication.
